TAX BENEFIT UPON THE AWARDS VESTING EQUAL TO THE TAX EFFECT OF THE UNDERLYING STOCKS FAIR MARKET VALUE. THE COMPANY HAD NET EXCESS TAX BENEFITS FROM EQUITY AWARDS OF $748 MILLION, $706 MILLION AND $643 MILLION IN 2015, 2014 AND 2013,

RESPECTIVELY, WHICH WERE REFLECTED AS INCREASES TO COMMON STOCK.

